nl.strohalm.cyclos.entities.accounts.transactions

Class Ticket

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.strohalm.cyclos.entities.Entity
      • nl.strohalm.cyclos.entities.accounts.transactions.Ticket
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PaymentRequestTicket, WebShopTicket

    public abstract class Ticket
extends Entity
    A ticket is used to validate external payments from clients not on whitelist. The web shop server (on the whitelist) must request a ticket to Cyclos, and pass this ticket to the client. When the client confirms all data, that ticket is passed back to Cyclos. If the ticket is not confirmed, it is marked as cancelled by the TicketExpirationListener
    Author:
    luis
